  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 198.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We wanted to see what beautiful Bendin looks like today, after not being there since the end of 1942.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We flew into Warsaw on a Tuesday-- on a Thursday-- and the next day we went by train to Katowice The train ride-- Katowice is not far from my hometown, which is a much bigger town.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The train ride was very comfortable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were only three people in the compartment that seats six people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The landscape was very bleak and gray.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The air was polluted to such a degree that my throat was scratchy, which lasted during most of our stay in Poland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Our companion on the train was a nice young Pole, an engineer by profession.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He was very anxious to start up a conversation right from the very beginning, as we settled ourselves on that train for a three and a half to four-hour journey to Katowice.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This young man seemed to be very self-conscious over the political situation in his country and very self-composed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Without telling him that we are Jews, he could not contain his emotions in wonderment and asked us, why does the whole world condemn the Poles for having helped the Germans exterminate the Jews?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Didn't the French, didn't the Romanians, didn't the Hungarians, the Lithuanians, and the Ukrainians help the Germans in their killings?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Didn't the Germans also kill the Poles?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, the tone of the conversation was a very polite one.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I just couldn't rebuke his argument by asking, why were most of the death factories in Poland-- such as Auschwitz, Treblinka, Majdanek, [INAUDIBLE], [INAUDIBLE], et cetera, et cetera?",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
